alvarionDeviceWirelessMIB.name: alvarionDeviceWirelessMIB
alvarionDeviceWirelessMIB.contactinfo: Alvarion Ltd. Postal: 21a HaBarzel St. P.O. Box 13139 Tel-Aviv 69710 Israel Phone: +972 3 645 6262

coDevWirSNRLevelNotificationEnabled.name: coDevWirSNRLevelNotificationEnabled
coDevWirSNRLevelNotificationEnabled.description: This attribute, when true, enables the generation of SNR level notifications.

coDevWirSNRLevelNotificationInterval.name: coDevWirSNRLevelNotificationInterval
coDevWirSNRLevelNotificationInterval.description: Specifies the interval in minutes between SNR level notifications.

coDevWirMinimumSNRLevel.name: coDevWirMinimumSNRLevel
coDevWirMinimumSNRLevel.description: A SNR level notification is generated each time the average SNR for all wireless stations connected to a VSC drops below this value.

coDevWirAssociationNotificationEnabled.name: coDevWirAssociationNotificationEnabled
coDevWirAssociationNotificationEnabled.description: Specifies if an association notification is generated when a new wireless client station associates with any VSC.

coDeviceWirelessInterfaceStatusEntry.name: coDeviceWirelessInterfaceStatusEntry
coDeviceWirelessInterfaceStatusEntry.description: An entry in the coDeviceWirelessInterfaceStatusTable. coDevDisIndex - Uniquely identifies a device in the MultiService Controller. coDevWirIfStaRadioIndex - Uniquely identifies a radio on the device.

coDevWirIfStaRadioIndex.name: coDevWirIfStaRadioIndex
coDevWirIfStaRadioIndex.description: Specifies the index of a radio on the device.

coDevWirIfStaOperatingMode.name: coDevWirIfStaOperatingMode
coDevWirIfStaOperatingMode.description: The current operating mode used by the radio.

coDevWirIfStaTransmitPower.name: coDevWirIfStaTransmitPower
coDevWirIfStaTransmitPower.description: Identifies the transmission power of the radio.

coDevWirIfStaOperatingChannel.name: coDevWirIfStaOperatingChannel
coDevWirIfStaOperatingChannel.description: Identifies the current operating channel of the radio.

coDevWirIfStaRadioMode.name: coDevWirIfStaRadioMode
coDevWirIfStaRadioMode.description: Identifies the current operating phy type of the radio.

coDevWirIfStaRadioType.name: coDevWirIfStaRadioType
coDevWirIfStaRadioType.description: Identifies the wireless device inside the Alvarion product.

coDevWirIfStaRadioOperState.name: coDevWirIfStaRadioOperState
coDevWirIfStaRadioOperState.description: When True indicates that the radio is enabled.

coDevWirIfStaNumberOfClient.name: coDevWirIfStaNumberOfClient
coDevWirIfStaNumberOfClient.description: Identifies the number of associated wireless clients.

coDevWirIfStaAutoChannelEnabled.name: coDevWirIfStaAutoChannelEnabled
coDevWirIfStaAutoChannelEnabled.description: When True indicates that the Auto Channel option is enabled.

coDevWirIfStaAutoChannelInterval.name: coDevWirIfStaAutoChannelInterval
coDevWirIfStaAutoChannelInterval.description: Time interval, in minutes, between auto rescanning of channels. Maximum is 1440 minutes (24 hours). A value of zero disables automatic rescanning of channels which means that the radio will automatically select a channel when the interface intializes and use that channel as long as the interface is operational.

coDevWirIfStaAutoPowerEnabled.name: coDevWirIfStaAutoPowerEnabled
coDevWirIfStaAutoPowerEnabled.description: When True indicates that the Auto Power option is enabled.

coDevWirIfStaAutoPowerInterval.name: coDevWirIfStaAutoPowerInterval
coDevWirIfStaAutoPowerInterval.description: Identifies the time interval, in minutes, between auto rescanning of channels. Maximum is 1440 minutes (24 hours).

coDevWirIfStaResetStats.name: coDevWirIfStaResetStats
coDevWirIfStaResetStats.description: Reset the wireless interface statistics. Reading this object will always return 'idle'.

coDeviceWirelessInterfaceStatsEntry.name: coDeviceWirelessInterfaceStatsEntry
coDeviceWirelessInterfaceStatsEntry.description: An entry in the coDeviceWirelessInterfaceStatsTable. coDevDisIndex - Uniquely identifies a device in the MultiService Controller. coDevWirIfStaRadioIndex - Uniquely identifies a radio on the device.

coDevWirIfStsTransmittedFragmentCount.name: coDevWirIfStsTransmittedFragmentCount
coDevWirIfStsTransmittedFragmentCount.description: This counter is incremented for each acknowledged MPDU with an individual address in the address 1 field or an MPDU with a multicast address in the address 1 field of type Data or Management.

coDevWirIfStsMulticastTransmittedFrameCo.name: coDevWirIfStsMulticastTransmittedFrameCount
coDevWirIfStsMulticastTransmittedFrameCo.description: This counter is incremented only when the multicast bit is set in the destination MAC address of a successfully transmitted MSDU. When operating as a STA in an ESS, where these frames are directed to the AP, this implies having received an acknowledgment to all associated MPDUs.

coDevWirIfStsFailedCount.name: coDevWirIfStsFailedCount
coDevWirIfStsFailedCount.description: This counter is incremented when an MSDU is not transmitted successfully due to the number of transmit attempts exceeding either coDot11ShortRetryLimit or coDot11LongRetryLimit.

coDevWirIfStsRetryCount.name: coDevWirIfStsRetryCount
coDevWirIfStsRetryCount.description: This counter is incremented when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after one or more retransmissions.

coDevWirIfStsMultipleRetryCount.name: coDevWirIfStsMultipleRetryCount
coDevWirIfStsMultipleRetryCount.description: This counter is incremented when an MSDU is successfully transmitted after more than one retransmission.

coDevWirIfStsFrameDuplicateCount.name: coDevWirIfStsFrameDuplicateCount
coDevWirIfStsFrameDuplicateCount.description: This counter is incremented when a frame is received and the Sequence Control field indicates that it is a duplicate.

coDevWirIfStsRTSSuccessCount.name: coDevWirIfStsRTSSuccessCount
coDevWirIfStsRTSSuccessCount.description: This counter is incremented when a CTS is received in response to an RTS.

coDevWirIfStsRTSFailureCount.name: coDevWirIfStsRTSFailureCount
coDevWirIfStsRTSFailureCount.description: This counter is incremented when a CTS is not received in response to an RTS.

coDevWirIfStsACKFailureCount.name: coDevWirIfStsACKFailureCount
coDevWirIfStsACKFailureCount.description: This counter is incremented when an ACK is not received when expected.

coDevWirIfStsReceivedFragmentCount.name: coDevWirIfStsReceivedFragmentCount
coDevWirIfStsReceivedFragmentCount.description: This counter is incremented for each successfully received MPDU of type Data or Management.

coDevWirIfStsMulticastReceivedFrameCount.name: coDevWirIfStsMulticastReceivedFrameCount
coDevWirIfStsMulticastReceivedFrameCount.description: This counter is incremented when a MSDU is received with the multicast bit set in the destination MAC address.

coDevWirIfStsFCSErrorCount.name: coDevWirIfStsFCSErrorCount
coDevWirIfStsFCSErrorCount.description: This counter is incremented when an FCS error is detected in a received MPDU.

coDeviceWirelessVscStatusTable.name: coDeviceWirelessVscStatusTable
coDeviceWirelessVscStatusTable.description: Device Virtual Service Communities status attributes.

coDeviceWirelessVscStatusEntry.name: coDeviceWirelessVscStatusEntry
coDeviceWirelessVscStatusEntry.description: An entry in the coDeviceWirelessVscStatusTable. coDevDisIndex - Uniquely identifies a device in the MultiService Controller. coDevWirIfStaRadioIndex - Uniquely identifies a radio on the device. coDevWirVscStaVscIndex - Uniquely identifies a Virtual Service Community on the device configuration file.

coDevWirVscStaVscIndex.name: coDevWirVscStaVscIndex
coDevWirVscStaVscIndex.description: Specifies the index of a Virtual Service Community in the device configuration file.

coDevWirVscStaMscVscIndex.name: coDevWirVscStaMscVscIndex
coDevWirVscStaMscVscIndex.description: Link to the Virtual Service Community in the device configuration file (coVscCfgIndex).

coDevWirVscStaBSSID.name: coDevWirVscStaBSSID
coDevWirVscStaBSSID.description: MAC Address assigned to the Virtual Service Community running on the specified radio.

coDevWirVscStaDefaultVLAN.name: coDevWirVscStaDefaultVLAN
coDevWirVscStaDefaultVLAN.description: VLAN ID assigned to a station after a successfull 802.11 association.

coDevWirVscStaMaximumNumberOfUsers.name: coDevWirVscStaMaximumNumberOfUsers
coDevWirVscStaMaximumNumberOfUsers.description: Maximum number of wireless client stations that can use the VSC on a specific radio.

coDevWirVscStaCurrentNumberOfUsers.name: coDevWirVscStaCurrentNumberOfUsers
coDevWirVscStaCurrentNumberOfUsers.description: Indicates the number of wireless client stations connected via this VSC.

coDevWirVscStaAverageSNR.name: coDevWirVscStaAverageSNR
coDevWirVscStaAverageSNR.description: Average SNR level for the users connected to this VSC.

coDevWirVscStaResetStats.name: coDevWirVscStaResetStats
coDevWirVscStaResetStats.description: Reset the Virtual Service Communities statistics. Read ing this object will always return 'idle'.

coDeviceWirelessVscStatsTable.name: coDeviceWirelessVscStatsTable
coDeviceWirelessVscStatsTable.description: Device Virtual Service Communities statistical attributes.

coDeviceWirelessVscStatsEntry.name: coDeviceWirelessVscStatsEntry
coDeviceWirelessVscStatsEntry.description: An entry in the coDeviceWirelessVscStatsTable. coDevDisIndex - Uniquely identifies a device in the MultiService Controller. coDevWirIfStaRadioIndex - Uniquely identifies a radio on the device. coDevWirVscStaVscIndex - Uniquely identifies a Virtual Service Community in the device configuration file.

coDevWirVscStsTxSecurityFilter.name: coDevWirVscStsTxSecurityFilter
coDevWirVscStsTxSecurityFilter.description: Number of outgoing packets dropped by the wireless security filters.

coDevWirVscStsRxSecurityFilter.name: coDevWirVscStsRxSecurityFilter
coDevWirVscStsRxSecurityFilter.description: Number of incoming packets dropped by the wireless security filters.

coDevWirVscStsWEPICVError.name: coDevWirVscStsWEPICVError
coDevWirVscStsWEPICVError.description: This counter increments when a frame is received with the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field set to one and the value of the ICV as received in the frame does not match the ICV value that is calculated for the contents of the received frame.

coDevWirVscStsWEPExcluded.name: coDevWirVscStsWEPExcluded
coDevWirVscStsWEPExcluded.description: This counter increments when a frame is received with the WEP subfield of the Frame Control field set to zero.

coDevWirVscStsTKIPICVError.name: coDevWirVscStsTKIPICVError
coDevWirVscStsTKIPICVError.description: Number of incoming packets with TKIP ICV errors.

coDevWirVscStsTKIPMICError.name: coDevWirVscStsTKIPMICError
coDevWirVscStsTKIPMICError.description: Number of incoming packets with TKIP MIC errors.

coDevWirVscStsTKIPCounterMeasure.name: coDevWirVscStsTKIPCounterMeasure
coDevWirVscStsTKIPCounterMeasure.description: Number of times the counter measure has been invoked.

coDevWirVscStsTKIPReplay.name: coDevWirVscStsTKIPReplay
coDevWirVscStsTKIPReplay.description: Number of incoming packets with TKIP replays.

coDevWirVscStsAESError.name: coDevWirVscStsAESError
coDevWirVscStsAESError.description: Number of incoming AES packets that were undecryptable.

coDevWirVscStsAESReplay.name: coDevWirVscStsAESReplay
coDevWirVscStsAESReplay.description: Number of incoming packets with AES replays.

coDeviceWirelessClientStatusEntry.name: coDeviceWirelessClientStatusEntry
coDeviceWirelessClientStatusEntry.description: An entry in the coDeviceWirelessClientStatusTable. coDevDisIndex - Uniquely identifies a device in the MultiService Controller. coDevWirIfStaRadioIndex - Uniquely identifies a radio on the device. coDevWirCliStaIndex - Uniquely identifies a wireless client using the specified radio on the device.

coDevWirCliStaIndex.name: coDevWirCliStaIndex
coDevWirCliStaIndex.description: Specifies the index of a wireless client using the specified radio in the device. The association ID is used for the index.

coDevWirCliStaMACAddress.name: coDevWirCliStaMACAddress
coDevWirCliStaMACAddress.description: Unique MAC Address assigned to the wireless device.

coDevWirCliStaVscIndex.name: coDevWirCliStaVscIndex
coDevWirCliStaVscIndex.description: Index of the Virtual Service Community in the device configuration file (coDevWirVscStaVscIndex).

coDevWirCliStaConnectTime.name: coDevWirCliStaConnectTime
coDevWirCliStaConnectTime.description: Elapsed time in seconds since a station has associated with this device.

coDevWirCliStaSNR.name: coDevWirCliStaSNR
coDevWirCliStaSNR.description: Relative strength of the signal level compared to the noise level.

coDevWirCliStaVLAN.name: coDevWirCliStaVLAN
coDevWirCliStaVLAN.description: VLAN ID of the associated station.

coDevWirCliStaTransmitRate.name: coDevWirCliStaTransmitRate
coDevWirCliStaTransmitRate.description: Current transmit rate of the associated station.

coDevWirCliStaReceiveRate.name: coDevWirCliStaReceiveRate
coDevWirCliStaReceiveRate.description: Current receive rate of the associated station.

coDevWirCliStaTrafficAuthorized.name: coDevWirCliStaTrafficAuthorized
coDevWirCliStaTrafficAuthorized.description: Current receive rate of the associated station.

coDevWirCliSta8021xAuthenticated.name: coDevWirCliSta8021xAuthenticated
coDevWirCliSta8021xAuthenticated.description: Current receive rate of the associated station.

coDevWirCliStaMACAuthenticated.name: coDevWirCliStaMACAuthenticated
coDevWirCliStaMACAuthenticated.description: Current receive rate of the associated station.

coDevWirCliStaMACFiltered.name: coDevWirCliStaMACFiltered
coDevWirCliStaMACFiltered.description: Current receive rate of the associated station.

coDevWirCliStaPhyType.name: coDevWirCliStaPhyType
coDevWirCliStaPhyType.description: Indicates the wireless mode used by the associated station.

coDevWirCliStaWPAType.name: coDevWirCliStaWPAType
coDevWirCliStaWPAType.description: Indicates the WPA/Encryption type used by the wireless station.

coDevWirCliStaIpAddress.name: coDevWirCliStaIpAddress
coDevWirCliStaIpAddress.description: Indicates the IP address of the wireless station.

coDevWirCliStaPowerSavingMode.name: coDevWirCliStaPowerSavingMode
coDevWirCliStaPowerSavingMode.description: If true, indicates that the wireless station is in power saving mode.

coDevWirCliStaWME.name: coDevWirCliStaWME
coDevWirCliStaWME.description: true : the wireless station sends QOS data frames. false : the wireless station sends data frames.

coDevWirCliStaPreviousAPAddress.name: coDevWirCliStaPreviousAPAddress
coDevWirCliStaPreviousAPAddress.description: Indicates the if the station roamed from this access point.

coDevWirCliStaResetStats.name: coDevWirCliStaResetStats
coDevWirCliStaResetStats.description: Reset the wireless client statistics. Reading this object will always return 'idle'. resetStats: reset the client statistics, resetRates: reset the client statistics rates, resetAll: perform both operations.
